{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-js","path":"/posts/just-mint/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"26dd85a0-d508-538f-a627-dc31a1abe463","html":"<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 960px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/8dcf2/gashapon.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/01472/gashapon.webp 240w,\n/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/222bd/gashapon.webp 480w,\n/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/620b9/gashapon.webp 960w,\n/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/95bc2/gashapon.webp 1400w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/webp\"\n        />\n        <source\n          srcset=\"/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/3bc27/gashapon.jpg 240w,\n/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/98431/gashapon.jpg 480w,\n/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/b3ee8/gashapon.jpg 960w,\n/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/8dcf2/gashapon.jpg 1400w\"\n          sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n          type=\"image/jpeg\"\n        />\n        <img\n          class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n          src=\"/static/0aa1b1a5ef8131918924298292f5c24c/b3ee8/gashapon.jpg\"\n          alt=\"Gashapon\"\n          title=\"Gashapon\"\n          loading=\"lazy\"\n        />\n      </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Loot boxes are a very common game mechanic, it lets game developers distribute content to players. These loot boxes are redeemable for in-game items called loot. Loots take meaning inside the game context and can range from skins to in-game advantage. They were inspired by Gashapon, a variety of vending machine-dispensed capsule toys popular in Asia.</p>\n<p>In very few years they have sprung in all game genres, creating a new business model paradigm, where revenue becomes a stream, instead of the single sold game, now users buy upon thoughts of dollars in-game items. This massive adoption is partly a response due to the rising development cost. They are also a great way to  promote users engagement. Itâ€™s estimated that by 2022, loot-boxes will have a market of 50 billion dollars. </p>\n<p>Just Mint is a set of tools for game developers that aim to shorten the gap between web3 and game developers. Simplifying the expression of in-game items as NFTs. Doing so empowers gamers, making them true owners of their won items. It gives developers a new needed source of revenue. And both gain access to the metaverse. Where their items can be expressed outside the game, and be materialized in a new reality.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://showcase.ethglobal.com/ethonline2021/just-mint\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Show case</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://youtu.be/xJiABLuD06g?t=1824\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Live demo</a></p>","fields":{"slug":"/posts/just-mint/","tagSlugs":["/tag/just-mint/","/tag/crypto/","/tag/english/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2021-11-09T23:46:37.121","description":"Brief introduction to just mint, ETH2021 finalists.","tags":["JustMint","Crypto","English"],"title":"Just Mint","socialImage":"/gashapon.jpg"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/posts/just-mint/"}}}